# Note: please use RFC 822 date syntax (see sample below)
# Entry-Date: The date and time that the Entry was added.
# Start-Date: The date and time that the propagation should be halted.
# Completion-Date: The date and time that the propgation should be resumed.
# Signed-Off-By: Your Name <yourhandle@gentoo.org>
# References: Any references (URL's, mailID's etc) for this block.
# Reason: List the reason for the block here.  Notice as in the sample below
#  If you wish to have a multiline reason you must use a space as a 
#  'line continuation'

Entry-Date: Thu, 11 Jan 2007 21:45:23 +0000
Start-Date: Thu, 11 Jan 2007 22:00:00 +0000
Completion-Date: Thu, 11 Jan 2007 23:00:00 +0000
Signed-Off-By: Alec Warner <antarus <at> gentoo.org>
References: http://article.gmane.org/gmane.linux.gentoo.devel/45310
Reason: The following is an example of a block for the block_sync file.
 This is a continuation line. Notice the leading space. It is still part
 of the Reason header.

#The above is the example block
